    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nVirtual lines above single line in a buffer are not always made visible after `<C-b>`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create an 'init.lua':\r\n    ```lua\r\n    local ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('virt-lines-in-single-line')\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'single line' })\r\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns_id, 0, 0, { virt_lines = { { { 'Above', 'String' } } }, virt_lines_above = true })\r\n    ```\r\n1. `nvim --clean -u path/to/init.lua`. The virtual line above is not visible, which seems to be expected (judging by #16166 and [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/15351#issuecomment-902107285)).\r\n2. Press `<C-b>`. Nothing happens.\r\n3. Press `<C-y>`. Virtual line appears.\r\n\r\nThe line can also be made visible with `<C-b>` if there are at least two buffer lines.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing `<C-b>` should consistently result into making virtual lines above first line visible. \n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2657+g9765efb40\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.8.1-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": "2024-03-28T11:50:04Z",
